# type: Content of: <chapter><section><title>
#: GettingStarted/monitoring-routers.xml:351
msgid "Monitoring Bandwidth / Traffic Rate"
msgstr "Supervision de la bande passante/trafic"

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: GettingStarted/monitoring-routers.xml:353
msgid "If you're monitoring bandwidth usage on your switches or routers using <ulink url=\"http://oss.oetiker.ch/mrtg/\"><application>MRTG</application></ulink>, you can have Nagios alert you when traffic rates exceed thresholds you specify. The &plugin-mrtgtraf; plugin (which is included in the Nagios plugins distribution) allows you to do this."
msgstr "Si vous supervisez l'usage de la bande passante de vos switchs et routeurs en utilisant  <ulink url=\"http://oss.oetiker.ch/mrtg/\"><application>MRTG</application></ulink>, vous pouvez utiliser Nagios pour alerter quand les valeurs dépassent un seuil que vous spécifiez. Le plugin &plugin-mrtgtraf; (inclus dans la distribution de splugins Nagios) vous permet de le faire."

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: GettingStarted/monitoring-routers.xml:359
msgid "You'll need to let the &plugin-mrtgtraf; plugin know what log file the <application>MRTG</application> data is being stored in, along with thresholds, etc. In my example, I'm monitoring one of the ports on a Linksys switch. The <application>MRTG</application> log file is stored in <filename>/var/lib/mrtg/192.168.1.253_1.log</filename>. Here's the service definition I use to monitor the bandwidth data that's stored in the log file..."
msgstr "Vous aurez besoin que le plugin &plugin-mrtgtraf; connaisse l'emplacement du fichier où <application>MRTG</application> stockes ses données, ainsi que les seuils, etc. Dans mon exemple, je supervise un des ports d'un switch Linksys. Le fichier de log de <application>MRTG</application> est stocké dans <filename>/var/lib/mrtg/192.168.1.253_1.log</filename>. Voici la définition de service que j'utilise pour superviser les données de bande passante stockées dans ce fichier... "

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><programlisting>
#: GettingStarted/monitoring-routers.xml:368
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"\n"
"define service{\n"
"   use                 generic-service ; Inherit values from a template\n"
"   host_name           linksys-srw224p\n"
"   service_description Port 1 Bandwidth Usage\n"
"   check_command       check_local_mrtgtraf!/var/lib/mrtg/192.168.1.253_1.log!AVG!1000000,2000000!5000000,5000000!10\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""
"\n"
"define service{\n"
"   use                 generic-service ; Inherit values from a template\n"
"   host_name           linksys-srw224p\n"
"   service_description Port 1 Bandwidth Usage\n"
"   check_command       check_local_mrtgtraf!/var/lib/mrtg/192.168.1.253_1.log!AVG!1000000,2000000!5000000,5000000!10\n"
"}\n"

# type: Content of: <chapter><section><para>
#: GettingStarted/monitoring-routers.xml:377
msgid "In the example above, the <filename>/var/lib/mrtg/192.168.1.253_1.log</filename> option that gets passed to the <emphasis>check_local_mrtgtraf</emphasis> command tells the plugin which <application>MRTG</application> log file to read from."
msgstr "Dans l'exemple ci-dessus, l'option <filename>/var/lib/mrtg/192.168.1.253_1.log</filename> passée à la commande <emphasis>check_local_mrtgtraf</emphasis> indique au plugin dans quel fichier de log <application>MRTG</application> il doit aller lire."

